Text.Value: Come and get us, you hairy bastards!

Text.Value: You're right - it's time.
One of us is getting out of here richer - I don't fight for free.
Fine. Follow my lead.
Hush, Olly.
Let's take them!
You can't leave us!
You're on your own.
We can handle ourselves - they got the drop on us before, but it's time for payback.

EditorData.NodeContext: assuring us he can help in a fight, determined

Text.Value: I know me and the boy are expendable. Comes with the job. But we can fight - no sense in leaving us behind.

EditorData.NodeContext: reasoning with us, sense of urgency, but understanding this is a perilous sitaution

Text.Value: There's another way out - follow me.
Your Zhentarim friends sent me to retrieve the cargo.
We don't have time. Hurry!

EditorData.NodeContext: urgency, panic - heavy emphasis on 'have' - we just asked for more time

Text.Value: There, you are fairly bought and paid for. Let's take them!

EditorData.NodeContext: Offering to pay for our help. Abrupt - wants to get this out of the way

Text.Value: We need to deal with those beasts now. They're hungry enough to brave the fire.
There's nothing in there that'll help - leave it!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Quiet conversation(?) - the afraid of the gnolls and don't want to provoke them

Text.Value: Ready? Let's kill those gnolls.
Thanks. Me and the boy will do what we can to help - we've still got some fight in us.
Damn it... must have dropped my purse.
I'm here for the cargo - rescuing you isn't part of the plan.
You'll only get in the way.
Bloody fool. I hope those monsters tear you to shreds!

EditorData.NodeContext: fury and fear - he's provoking a pack of monstrous gnolls as he says this, or preparing to, by throwing a molotov cocktail
EditorData.StateChangeTags: Throwing Molotov cocktail at the end of the dialog.

Text.Value: Across the chasm? You might have got in that way, but you're stuck with us now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confused at the suggestion that we can leave across a 'chasm'. Urgent, panicked

Text.Value: Hold the line while I prepare for the fight.
Fine. Follow my lead.
You'll only get in the way.
If you're here to help, get to the fight quickly!

EditorData.NodeContext: shouting to player - at least one of the player's companions is already in a fight with nearby gnolls
EditorData.logicalname: Greeting (while other players are fighting gnolls)

Text.Value: You misunderstand. I'm not going to leave you behind - I'm going to kill you.
Half-devil you might be, but I don't see any wings.

EditorData.NodeContext: mocking, but desperate rather than smug

Text.Value: All right. Hold the line while I prepare for battle.
Aye, that we can do. The fire won't hold them forever though. Be quick about it.
Right you are. If we get out of this, I owe you.
Counter-offer. You fight with us, or you die with us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Making a quick decision - and possibly a foolish one. He's going to provoke some monstrous gnolls to attack, hoping they'll kill us

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: he throws fire directly at the gnolls, provoking them into attacking

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Showing the gnolls at the entrance of the cave.

Text.Value: When the fighting starts, we'll be right alongside you.

Synopsis: One of a pair of Zhentarim agents trapped in a cave by gnolls. A veteran mercenary, tough, and above all else a survivor. The rest of their crew are dead. Rugan here is the senior agent of the two, and he's grimly determined to survive this terrible situation.
